---
description: To run shell commands, use `./just-agents <cmd> <args>`.
alwaysApply: true
---

**CRITICAL:** You may ONLY run commands with `./just-agents <cmd> <args>`.
- **List all allowed commands:** `./just-agents help`
- ALWAYS start your session with `./just-agents help`


- **NEVER** edit `just-agents.Justfile` without asking first (unless the user explicitly asked for a change to agent commands there).

- **Git / merge:** never run `./just-agents git-dangerously` with `fetch`, `checkout`, `switch`, `pull`, `merge`, `push`, `rebase`, or similar merge/remote work unless the user **explicitly** instructed a merge (see `.cursor/skills/tao-git-workflow/SKILL.md` and comments in `just-agents.Justfile`).

- **Git / merge:** after merging **`main` into a feature branch**, run **`./just-agents prep-commit`** until green before squash merge, push, or PR handoff (see `tao-git-workflow` and `prep-feature-branch-merge`).

- **Justfile Documentation:**
    - For a succinct summary, first see: https://cheatography.com/linux-china/cheat-sheets/justfile/
    - **If** you need more details, see:: https://just.systems/man/en/

Full package layout, testing commands, and Cursor file map: **`AGENTS.md`** (section *Cursor: rules, commands, skills*).
